<entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"
    xml:id="entry_fæzdon" xml:lang="os">
    <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma">
        <orth>fæzdon</orth>
    </form>
    <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal">
        <orth>fæzdonæ</orth>
    </form>
    <sense>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
            <q>вымя</q>
        </cit>
        <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
            <q>udder</q>
        </cit>
    </sense>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>(sæǧ) ūzgæ-ūzgæ, fæzdon nærstæj racæwy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>(коза) идет покачиваясь, с набухшим выменем</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>a goat is walking and swaying, with a swollen udder</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 164</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>sæwtyl уn læværdtoj būræ næl fystæ, fæzdættyl ta kwīst dalystæ</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>за козлов ему давали желтых баранов, а за (коз) с выменем — годовалых ягнят</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>for goats he was given yellow rams, and for goats with udders — one-year-old
                    lambs</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 114</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <cit type="exampleGroup">
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>(sæǧ) ūzgæ-ūzgæ, fæzdon nærstæj racæwy</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>(коза) идет покачиваясь, с набухшим выменем</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>a goat is walking and swaying, with a swollen udder</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 164</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
        <cit type="example">
            <quote>sæwtyl уn læværdtoj būræ næl fystæ, fæzdættyl ta kwīst dalystæ</quote>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru">
                <q>за козлов ему давали желтых баранов, а за (коз) с выменем — годовалых ягнят</q>
            </cit>
            <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <q>for goats he was given yellow rams, and for goats with udders — one-year-old
                    lambs</q>
            </cit>
            <bibl>
                <ref target="#src_ЮОПам."/>
                <biblScope>III 114</biblScope>
            </bibl>
        </cit>
    </cit>
    <etym xml:lang="ru">Сопоставляется с <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>pistān</w><gloss><q>женская грудь</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>вымя</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>pīstän</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pēšten</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
            ><lang/><w>vistān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><lang/><w>pezïn</w><gloss><q>вымя</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>’stn-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>fštāna-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>stāna-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                    ><lang/><w>st'in</w><gloss><q>женская грудь</q></gloss></mentioned>. Однако
        звуковые взаимоотношения иранских форм, равно как этимология слова — не ясны. %sFr. Müller%s
                (<bibl><author>Müller</author><ref target="#ref_WZKM"/><biblScope>VI
            184</biblScope></bibl>) возводил к %i*рауаstāna%i (от %i*payah-%i ‘молоко’), что
        вызывает возражения (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."
            /><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>). Для осетинского %ifæzdon%i всего удобнее было бы
        исходить из %i*payaz-dāna-%i буквально „вместилище (%idāna-%i) молока (%ipayaz-%i)“ или из
        %i*pat-dāna%i с последующей закономерной диссимиляцией %itd%i → %izd%i. Ср. <ref type="xr"
            target="#entry_fædæg"/> ‘сосок’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II
                86</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II
                241</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author><ref target="#ref_BSOAS"
                /><biblScope>XIV 484</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">It is compared with <mentioned xml:lang="fa"
                    ><lang/><w>pistān</w><gloss><q>breast</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="fa"><w/><gloss><q>udder</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ydg"
                ><lang/><w>pīstän</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sgy"
            ><lang/><w>pēšten</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="srh"
            ><lang/><w>vistān</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="wbl"
                    ><lang/><w>pezïn</w><gloss><q>udder</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
            xml:lang="sog"><lang/><w>’stn-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                ><lang/><w>fštāna-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>stāna-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"
                    ><lang/><w>st'in</w><gloss><q>breast</q></gloss></mentioned>. However, the sound
        relationships of the Iranian forms, as well as the etymology of the word, are not clear.
        %sFr. Müller%s (<bibl><author>Müller</author><ref target="#ref_WZKM"/><biblScope>VI
                184</biblScope></bibl>) traced it back to %i*рауаstāna%i (from %i*payah-%i ‘milk’),
        what is objectionable (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Hübschmann._PSt."
            /><biblScope>41</biblScope></bibl>). For Ossetic %ifæzdon%i it would be most convenient
        to proceed from %i*payaz-dāna-%i literally ‘container (%idāna-%i) for milk (%ipayaz-%i)’ or
        from %i*pat-dāna%i with the following regular dissimilation %itd%i → %izd%i. Cf. <ref
            type="xr" target="#entry_fædæg"/> ‘сосок’.%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"
                /><biblScope>II 86</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Morgenstierne._IIFL"/><biblScope>II 241</biblScope></bibl>. —
                <bibl><author>Gershevitch</author><ref target="#ref_BSOAS"/><biblScope>XIV
                484</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
</entry>
